				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> De 1856</date>.</p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As I promised you to write<lb/> but did not find an opportunity before&#44; I now take<lb/> my <sic>leasure</sic> to devote it to your correspondence.<lb/>  I would furnish you with more good and far<lb/> more interested articles that the one I gave<lb/> you&#44; but alas&#33; Druble<add>&#63;</add> for support do not<lb/> permit my mind to sit down and write<lb/> with a clear and correct attention&#44; in the<lb/> first place&#44; I am now out of business and<lb/> having no means for support so that I can<lb/> not sit down and write articles&#44; but if wish<lb/> to have some and can make some allowance<lb/> I will furnish you as above.  The article I gave<lb/> you&#44; you can publish in your publication&#44; but<lb/> for the next&#44; after you communication I am willing<lb/> and will act.  Please direct a note to&#44; as below.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Your humble &#38; ob&#39;t sevt.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">A. Henry Dreyer</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>35 Beckman Street</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
